intro: Dicrastylis corymbosa, commonly known as the clustered star sedge, is a perennial herbaceous plant native to Australia. It belongs to the family Cyperaceae, which includes sedges and related plants. The plant is characterized by its grass-like appearance, with narrow, strap-shaped leaves and small, clustered flower heads. It typically grows in wet or swampy areas, thriving in moist, well-drained soils. Dicrastylis corymbosa is often found in coastal and inland regions, contributing to the biodiversity of wetland ecosystems.
